main event: An unidentified flying object was observed in Silver Spring, Maryland on November 27, 1966, visible for about 15 seconds.
interesting points: The object was observed glowing and moving in a straight line,The sighting occurred at approximately 30 to 40 degrees above the horizon,It was determined to be probably a meteor or piece of space debris,The object was lost from sight over trees,The report indicated no photographs or physical evidence were collected.
sighted object: a glowing object moving in a straight line
witness description: A student who sounded intelligent, sober, and interested.
